    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Kyle Tucker** (76.67) and **Jackson Merrill** (70.91) serving as our undisputed pillars of offensive production. **Kyle Tucker** benefits significantly from a favorable matchup against Colin Rea, where a combination of wind-out conditions and an ideal cleanup spot boosts his efficiency despite the SP_xERA hovering in a neutral range. **Jackson Merrill** mirrors this output, as his dynamic platoon advantage against Zac Gallen provides a substantial ceiling increase. Meanwhile, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.40) anchors the middle of our order, showing excellent plate discipline metrics against the lefty Cantillo, making him a cornerstone play in a game where we expect high-frequency contact.\n\nWe are navigating a few tactical tightropes today, most notably with **Gunnar Henderson** (52.11) and **Dominic Smith** (41.31), who are both forced to contend with elite opposition in Garrett Crochet and Zack Wheeler, respectively. **Gunnar Henderson** remains a start despite the steep SP skill penalty because his park factor is exceptionally high, offsetting the projected struggle against a tough lefty. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (47.28); while he possesses legitimate power upside, his lack of stolen base utility and a lower efficiency score compared to **Jacob Wilson** (53.92) kept him on the pine. We are prioritizing **Jacob Wilson**'s positional flexibility and lineup slot over **Marcell Ozuna**\u2019s raw output, as we continue to hunt for category efficiency in the scarce SB environment. \n\nCaution is advised regarding the \"Lineup Pending\" designations for **Drake Baldwin**, **Andy Pages**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Dominic Smith**, and **Josh Jung**. While our projections account for historical tendencies, a move down the order for **Andy Pages** or **Drake Baldwin** could see their scores dip below our marginal threshold. Additionally, while **Heliot Ramos** (45.93) has a favorable SB outlook due to the opposing battery's slow delivery, he faces an uphill battle against Eury P\u00e9rez. We will be monitoring the official lineups closely; if any of our assumed batting orders shift unfavorably, we are prepared to pivot to high-floor reserves like **Coby Mayo** if pinch-hit utility or late-inning platoon shifts arise.",
